  <member name="POINTER_INPUT_TYPE.PT_POINTER">
    <summary>
      <para>Generic pointer type. This type never appears in pointer messages or pointer data. Some data query functions allow the caller to restrict the query to specific pointer type. The <b>PT_POINTER</b> type can be used in these functions to specify that the query is to include pointers of all types</para>
    </summary>
